author: Terry St. John
title: HTA Junior Fall Festival begins Saturday, October 24
text:
HTA Junior Fall Festival Terry St. John The Houston Tennis Association Junior Fall Festival will be held October 24-25 at Lee LeClear Tennis Center .
Arya Shetty of Cypress is the top seed in the super championship boys 16s, and Jordan Laner of The Woodlands is the top seed in the championship boys 16s.
Open girls top seeds are 16s—Natalia Castellanos Garcia of The Woodlands and 14s—Emma Kesterson of New Braunfels.
Other top seeds in the boys divisions are: 16 non-qualified—SimonGabriel Diaz of Missouri City; 14 qualified—Trenton Bui of Houston; 14 non-qualified—Eli Cowan of Bellaire; 12 qualified—Corbin Barrus of Houston; and 12 non-qualified—Joseph Enriquez of Missouri City.
Anna Bouleau of Katy is the No. 1 seed in the girls 12 qualified division.
Tournament viewing is free. For more information call the HTA at 281-580-8313 or visit www.houstontennis.org .
